### Gradient of the output (fully connected) layer's bias

Given a batch of samples \((\mathbf{x}^{(j,n)},y^{(j,n)})\), the cross-entropy loss is readily computed as

\[\mathcal{L}_{\textbf{CE}}=-\frac{1}{Bl}\sum_{j=1}^{l}\sum_{n=1}^{B}\log\frac{ \exp\left(q_{y^{(j,n)}}^{(j,n)}\right)}{\sum_{c=1}^{C}\exp\left(q_{c}^{(j,n)} \right)}=\frac{1}{Bl}\sum_{j=1}^{l}\sum_{n=1}^{B}\mathcal{L}_{\textbf{CE}}^{( j,n)},\ \ \ y^{(j,n)}\in[C]\] (13)

